cs.CL, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is about a visual analysis tool for exploring learned representations in large language models, which are typically used for natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on NLP and related areas. The paper also discusses the importance of interactive tools for gaining intuition about the model-internal reasoning process, which suggests a potential fit with the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of self-attention mechanisms and inductive biases, which are topics that fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of annotated datasets to match human-specified inputs, which is related to Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
